CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 5, 1955, pg. 12A, reads: "The Last Trip - City police stand guard as friends carry the casket containing the remains of Howard C. McKinney, Pittsburgh's famed youth leader and founder of Hill City, to its final resting place. Funeral services were held Saturday from Central Baptist Church where the deceased taught Sunday school and served as superintendent of the Sunday school for a number of years. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pallbearers carrying casket through two rows of police officers raising batons, in front of Central Baptist Church for funeral of Howard C. McKinney
